&lt;p&gt;OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY ASSISTANT&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MENTAL HEALTH&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BAND 3&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Part-time or Full-time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;OLDER PEOPLE IN-PATIENT SERVICES&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Functional and/or Dementia wards&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an innovative and creative Occupational Therapy Assistant to join our older people wards at Thurrock Community Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ideally you will have experience in mental health and have excellent communication and organisational skills. You will form an integral member of a dynamic team currently developing intervention pathways and expanding our interventions for people with Dementia and people with functional mental illnesses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work with a team of people under the expert direction of a qualified Occupational Therapist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Knowledge of mental health would help and an interest in ‘doing’ would be of benefit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return of your commitment, the Trust offers a wide range of training opportunities and career development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EPUT are looking for motivated staff who shares our Trust values of Open, Compassionate and Empowering. In return, EPUT can offer you a range of benefits and development including;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Season Ticket Loans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts for staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent Training facilities and opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Buying and Selling annual leave scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to work bank shifts and expand knowledge and experience in other areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary Sacrifice schemes including lease cars and Cycle to Work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal queries and visits are welcome&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal chat please phone Ellen van den Hoven, Head OT for Adult In-patient services on 078111 66399 arrangements for speaking to the local Occupational Therapist can be organised.&lt;/p&gt;
